---
description: Coins on mobile must use in-app purchases only
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Coins, top-ups, and coin packages inside the mobile app must use platform in-app purchases only.

Rules:
- on Android, coin purchases inside the app must use Google Play billing / IAP
- on iOS, coin purchases inside the app must use Apple in-app purchases / IAP
- do not use Stripe for in-app coin purchases
- do not route in-app coin purchase flows to external web checkout
- do not implement coins as a normal external payment flow inside the mobile app
- preserve the existing UI while wiring purchase logic
- connect existing coin buttons to the correct mobile purchase flow
- keep package identifiers, product mapping, and receipt handling grounded in the real codebase
- do not invent fake purchase success states
- do not mark purchases complete without real verification logic
- do not expose secrets in client code

Allowed:
- connect coin buttons to IAP handlers
- add missing purchase handlers
- add guards, loading states, and error handling without changing UI
- improve receipt flow and purchase state handling
- fix broken purchase wiring with minimal diff

Default behavior:
coins inside the mobile app use platform IAP only.
